There is a mechanism using `local_path` to allow a new worker-side path to be specified by a staging mechanism. I've made PR #808 which makes this usable with all file schemes.

It might be enough that you can use that instead of `task_path` and `in_task`: once you set `local_path`, then asking for `file.filepath` will return that overridden path, which is what you're doing here. I'm a little unsure if you need to separately track `in_task` here. The other staging mechanisms don't do so.

