The return type of this closure is consistent across the branches, so we don't need the boxing or the future-result type ascriptions and stuff. This could actually just be:
```rust
            .then(|primary_result| match primary_result {
              Ok(primary_success) => {
                debug!("primary request eventually SUCCEEDED after secondary failed");
                Ok(primary_success)
              },
                Err(primary_failure) => {
                debug!("primary request eventually FAILED after secondary failed");
                Err(primary_failure)
              })
```

or even simpler:
```rust
.then(|primary_result| {
  if primary_result.is_ok() {
    debug!("primary request eventually SUCCEEDED after secondary failed");
  } else {
    debug!("primary request eventually FAILED after secondary failed");
  }
  primary_result
})

